  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Provision of Integrated package of emergency Education, WASH and Child Protection in Bari, Sanaag and Sool regions of Puntland</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">TASS proposes this project to improve access to quality education, protection and WASH services for drought affected communities in emergency situation in Bari and Nugal regions of Puntland-State of Somalia, the project directly addresses the needs of the target communities mainly children and women. This project will create protective environment for children free from child abuse, improves hygiene/sanitation in schools and also provides quality education through provision of integrated services.

Protection proposed activities TASS offers survivor centered protection support services, IDTR, school children Rights club establishment, holding CP/GBV community dialogue, training of CECs, CPCs on Disaster Risk Management, (DRR), CP/GBV prevention and response techniques, PSS, Child safeguarding, school management, psycho social individual and group counseling, strengthening referral pathways, CP/GBV awareness sessions for prevention purpose and disseminate available protection services, mapping referral pathways and monitoring and reporting of protection violations for action and improving coordination among line ministries and cluster organizations for information sharing. 

Education, TASS will undertake school feeding program, provision of teaching /learning materials, provision of sanity kits for adolescent girls, construction of 3 temporary learning classes, CEC training, provision of teachers&#x2019; incentives and back to school campaigns. WASH TASS will implement the following activities construction of 20 gender segregated twin latrines with hand washing facilities in ten schools, provision water storage, provision of psychosocial support to students in schools and building the capacity on and setting school improvement plan, PHAST and CHAST training. 

To ensure inclusivity and sustainability of the project TASS will improve the coordination and information sharing with the concerned line ministries ministry of education and ministry of women (MoWDAFA , WASH/Protection and Education clusters, UNOCHA and other community stakeholders including school teachers, parents and as well as community structures women, youth, religious leaders, and CSOs.</narrative>
  </description>
